//Fracture – Patella AO 34


Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 04 - Bones of Knee MRI
When I select the radio button 'Finding'
Then 'Finding' dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Fracture – Patella AO 34' from the Finding dropdown
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And '34A : Extraarticular' radio button is enabled
And '34B: Partial articular' radio button is enabled
And '34C: Complete articular' radio button is enabled
And 'Fracture patella, not further specified' radio button is enabled

When I select '34A : Extraarticular' radio button
Then '34A1: Avulsion fracture' checkbox is enabled
And 'a: Proximal pole' radio button is enabled
And '' radio button is enabled
And '' radio button is enabled
And '' radio button is enabled

When '34B: Partial articular' radio button
And '34B1: Lateral' radio button is enabled
And '34B2: Medial' radio button is enabled

When I select '34B1: Lateral' radio button
Then '34B1.1: Sagittal fracture, 1 fragment' radio button is enabled
And '34B1.2: Sagittal fracture, multifragmentary' radio button is enabled

When I select '34B2: Medial' radio button
Then '34B2.1: Sagittal fracture, 1 fragment' radio button is enabled
And '34B2.2: Sagittal fracture, multifragmentary' radio button is enabled

When '34C: Complete articular' radio button
Then '34C1: Horizontal fracture, 1 fragment' radio button is enabled
And '34C2: Horizontal fracture, 3 fragment with wedge shape' radio button is enabled
And '34C3: Multifragmentary' radio button is enabled


When I select 'Fracture patella, not further specified' radio button
Then 'Fracture older, consolidated' radio button is enabled
And 'Suspicion of' radio button is enabled
